phrases: We are here to support you.
If something is bothering you, let me know.
I trust you, Subaru-chan, Erika-chan, Gon-chan, and Sayu-chan, too.
That is why you are so vulnerable, Chief.
Honoka-chan, you have a black aura coming out.
But I do yell at slacking people.
Back to working on the floor, then!
You are done for the day, are not you?
You look like you are having fun.
You are out of the hospital already?
Pretty much what you would expect, right?
You are still wrapped in bandages!
So you are worried about me?
Do not come in without permission!
Well, I could not wait to see Misa-chan at Maid Latte.
It is the celebrity school where all the rich boys and girls go.
It has the kind of people we try our best not to associate with.
What kind of ruckus are you making in the middle of the street?!
I am the Student Council President of Seika High School, Ayuzawa Misaki.
One of your students punched me.
I had heard that Seika High School is a savage place, and it would seem that the rumor is true.
I need to think about what sort of apology this will require.
Why should we apologize to you?
I am telling you to apologize for hitting him!
You are the one that punched us!
Think of the trouble you are causing for everyone here!
Only idiots hit other people out of anger.
Looks like it is not worth talking to them right now.
We will be waiting for you at Miyabigaoka anytime.
If you do not have any intention of apologizing, then I will bring this issue to the administration.
What are you going to do if this case turns out to be a big problem?
And right when Seika's image is starting to get better, too...
Your hard work will go to waste.
That is what I said, but I cannot imagine them obediently apologizing.
I do not have the time to be thinking about unnecessary things.
I am sorry, could someone help me with these?
He got me all confused, but he is like that to everyone!
Finding that out makes me feel much better!
I cannot follow what is going on.
Something is completely messed up right now.
He is definitely some kind of perverted alien!
Seriously, what is wrong with you?
I am coming with you since it sounds fun.
I have not ridden a bus in a while.
More like, why do we have to apologize to them?
Like I said, if you are so against apologizing, then tell me what caused the fight.
I bet it would be cool to be able to play it.
Heck, you are even bad at Othello.
That store belongs to my family.
It is no place for filth like you.
He goes and says something like that.
How could we apologize to him?
But, you are telling us to apologize anyways.
Miyabigaoka's building is stuck-up no matter how many times I see it.
So you are finally here, Seika High School.
I see an extra face here.
Is he the Vice President or something?
No, I am here to study sociology.
I have been looking forward to how you will show me your sincerity.
Did you not come to apologize?
This is why I hate brainless poor people.
We will continue this in the Student Council Room.
So you called our students flies just like that.
I am fine with continuing this in the Student Council Room.
I do not mind making this an official issue.
However, I would like you to apologize to us first!
Because you were the first to insult our students, causing them to punch you.
Honestly, I want to beat the crap out of you, too.
Nothing let us you call the students of Seika flies.
I demand an apology from you.
What is wrong with calling a fly a fly?
How about we settle this with a game of chess then?
If you can beat me in this game, then I will admit that Seika's students are not flies.
We have never played chess before!
I hate how he says that so arrogantly.
Then I guess I will play.
I have played a bit in the past, so you do not have to.
I placed fourth in this year's national tournament.
So, I better go easy on you a little.
If I win against you playing seriously, you have to admit that Seika's Prez is a butterfly rather than a fly.
How could I possibly lose when I am playing seriously?
Is not he losing his nerve?
Could it be that Usui-san is good?
You are bothering the other passengers.
How could we possibly gauge an individual's worth through a game like this?
I do not want to be even breathing the same air!
That made us feel a lot better!
You guys should not get too carried away, alright?
You are at fault, too, so if something like this happens again-
We will ask for your help.
Gosh, they are such a hassle.
To me, you are a bigger hassle.
Anyways, is Miyabigaoka filled with students like him?
But then, I am sure there are better guys that that, and there must be troubles that rich people face that I cannot imagine.
Therefore, I am here to request that you, Prez, demand an apology from Seika High School.
Seika is more savage and dangerous than the rumors say.
Besides, a girl being President in the midst of boys is proof of a lack of motivation and an atrophy of order.
Miyabigaoka's Student Council President is here.
He is the heir to the Igarashi Foundation.
I have seen him on a magazine before.
Is he here to complain to Misaki?
Misaki-san will take care of him.
I am the Student Council President of Miyabigaoka, Igarashi Tora.
What brings Miyabigaoka's Student Council President here?
I am sorry for our student's insolent behavior.
I have suggested to the Principal that he should be expelled from the school.
We do share part of the blame for actually punching him, too.
It was not anything you had to come all the way here for, too.
Then I may cancel his expulsion?
I am glad to hear that.
Still, you are exactly as the rumors had said.
You are fair, thoughtful, and always think foremost of the students.
What did you do that for!?
Those guys are goofing off again.
Do not I always tell you to use that extra energy for studying?
I totally forgot about President Igarashi.
Someone so strong and beautiful is truly a dependable person.
You see, I came here today with a request for you other than the apology.
Will you join us at Miyabigaoka's Student Council?
Um, I do not understand what you are saying.
I have never heard of a student working for student councils of two different schools.
Naturally, we will provide the uniform and anything else you need.
No, unfortunately, my family is very poor.
I cannot afford to go to a school with expensive tuition like Miyabigaoka.
We will prepare a special student loan.
Considering your excellence, I am sure you will even be exempted from paying it back, too.
I look forward to hearing your favorable reply.
I do not think I will...
In the past, Seika High School was nothing but a problem.
But now, the entire student council is working together to create a better school.
You have made a wonderful school.
Man, it was hot in there.
No wonder it is a poor kids' school.
They do not even have the air conditioning on.
She nailed him straight in the neck.
I did not expect that woman to be that interesting.
Let us see what she does next.
You keep your eyes on her.
We cannot go in if it is ladies only day.
I cannot see anything because of the fogged glass.
Allow me to take you to your seat.
This is only possible because of her.
After all, she is a huge hit with the ladies.
Come to think of, this is the first time there are so many girls around.
You seem to be having fun, Misaki-kun.
Of course, since I am so popular.
A girl being popular with girls?
I am already a guy at heart.
It feels good to be acknowledged by others.
If all guys were like this, I would be fine with them.
Like being kind, reliable, and gentlemanly.
Someone like the president of Miyabigaoka?
Why are you brining up President Igarashi?
Better yet, stop talking and move your hands.
We are still having trouble choosing.
Then let us choose it with me.
I wish I had an older brother like this.
But, Misaki-kun might actually be a younger brother type.
No, I would say you are thinking too much.
He is got to be the dominant type.
But is not it nice to have that type be passive once in a while, too?
I do not understand them at all.
They have a sense of hygiene and charm that guys do not.
I wonder if I can keep dressing as a guy from now on, too.
Do you know what they mean?
Do you want me to show you?
What are you doing with your shirt off?
I got sweaty, so I wanted to take my undershirt off.
You should get changed, too, Misaki-kun.
I will get changed after you go home.
What is the matter with guys stripping together?
How about I undress you, Misaki-kun?
Apparently that is what dominant is.
How much do you need to confuse me before you are satisfied?
I have had enough of you messing around with me.
Here is the report on Ayuzawa Misaki, President.
You have got to be kidding.
She really is the best woman.
I just came up with the best welcoming event for her.
I never thought I would receive such a great offer to attend Miyabigaoka.
But if I transfer, Seika will return to the way it used to be, and the remaining girls will be scared and shiver.
You are such a worrywart, Prez.
You cannot make up your mind, not because of yourself, but because of the girls that get left behind?
If you go to Miyabigaoka, I wonder if you will stop working at Maid Latte as well.
I already told you that I have had enough of you messing around with me.
